[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mtika[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpnfn0ohvg[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA file path traversal vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCVE-class security issue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was detected during [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing of the TikaAppUntarringFuzzer. The Jazzer fuzzer's security sanitizers [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentified an attempt to create or access a file path outside of the intended [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory structure [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp8534309584543316345/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggering a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception. This indicates that the Apache Tika [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntarring functionality may be vulnerable to path traversal attacks when processing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaliciously crafted tar archives.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue represents a **File Path Traversal** vulnerability, which is a critical [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity concern. This type of vulnerability allows an attacker to access files and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectories stored outside the intended target directory by manipulating file paths[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min archive entries.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Details[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring fuzzing execution of the `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`, the Jazzer security [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer detected a file path traversal attempt at the following location:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Problematic Path**: [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp8534309584543316345/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Detection Point**: [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Deduplication Token**: `0e51155e1f0e30d4`[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe exception was thrown when the code attempted to perform a file operation [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlikely creating or writing to a file[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a path that violated security [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundaries. The Jazzer sanitizer specifically intercepted this through its [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pathFirstArgHook` at line [0m[1;36m177[0m[39m of `FilePathTraversal.java`.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Call Stack Analysis[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability manifests through the following execution path:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Point**: `com.example.TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Processing Layer**: `com.example.TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m84[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Vulnerable Component**: `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m47[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Security Intercept**: [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.pathFirstArgHook` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Configuration**: The fuzzer was running with the following parameters:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - RSS limit: [0m[1;36m2560[0m[39m MB[0m                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Input source: `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Instrumentation Coverage**: The fuzzer successfully instrumented multiple [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelevant classes including:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFilePathTraversal sanitizer, indicating comprehensive monitoring of file system [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand the complete scope of this vulnerability, the following components [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be thoroughly examined:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Primary Target**: `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mspecifically around [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m47[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - This is where the untarring operation is performed and where the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerable file path operation occurs.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Archive Processing**: [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar.TarArchiveInputStream` - [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResponsible for reading tar archive entries[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar.TarArchiveEntry` - Represents [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindividual tar entries and their metadata, including file paths[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Path Validation**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How tar entry names/paths are extracted and processed[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether any validation or sanitization of entry paths is performed before file[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How relative paths, parent directory references [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and absolute paths in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtar entries are handled[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **File System Operations**:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.io.FileUtils` - Used for file operations during extraction[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `org.apache.commons.io.file.PathUtils` - Path manipulation utilities that may [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe involved in the vulnerable operation[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Test Case Analysis**: The input test case at `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m` that triggered this [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability should be examined to understand what specific tar archive structure [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor entry naming pattern caused the traversal attempt.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability appears to allow tar archives with specially crafted entry names [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mpotentially containing path traversal sequences like `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to write files outside[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe intended extraction directory, which could lead to arbitrary file write [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapabilities on the system.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mp.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbasePath.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:                        [0m[32m"fetchKey must resolve to be a descendant of the [0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:            p = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfetchKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-batch/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/batch/fs/FSUtil.jav[0m[1;92ma:197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m203[0m               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:    public static Path [0m[1;35mresolveRelative[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath p, String other[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mp.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/io/FilenameUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m112[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:     * This is a duplication of the algorithm and functionality[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:     * available in commons io FilenameUtils.  If Java's File were[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:     * able handle Windows file paths correctly in linux,[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:     * we wouldn't need this.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:     * The goal of this is to get a filename from a path.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:     * The package parsers and some other embedded doc[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:     * extractors could put anything into TikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:     * If a careless client used that filename as if it were a[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:     * filename and not a path when writing embedded files,[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:     * bad things could happen.  Consider: [0m[32m"../../../my_ppt.ppt"[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:     * Consider using this in combination with [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link #[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:     * @param path path to strip[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:     * @return empty string or a filename, never null[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:    public static String [0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath == null || [0m[1;35mpath.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:            return StringUtils.EMPTY;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:        int unix = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:        int windows = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39m"\\"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95msome[0m[39m macintosh file names are stored with : as the delimiter[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95malso[0m[39m necessary to properly handle C:somefilename[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:        int colon = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m":"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:        String cand = [0m[1;35mpath.substring[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mMath.max[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcolon, [0m[1;35mMath.max[0m[1;39m([0m[39munix, windows[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m +[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcand.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m".."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcand.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"."[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:            return StringUtils.EMPTY;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:        return cand;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy for Path Traversal Vulnerability in TikaUntar[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Analysis Summary[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Root Cause:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability in `TikaUntar.jav[0m[1;92ma:43[0m[39m` occurs because the code resolves tar entry[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames against the extraction directory and normalizes the path, but **never [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidates** that the final path remains within the intended extraction directory. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis allows malicious tar archives to write files outside the target directory [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relative path traversal sequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/../../etc/[0m[95mpasswd[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Absolute paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mevil.txt[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Complex path manipulations that escape after normalization[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Key Evidence from Codebase:**[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **FileSystemFetcher.jav[0m[1;92ma:79[0m[39m** demonstrates the correct validation pattern used [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melsewhere in Tika:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mp.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbasePath.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"path must be descendant of basePath"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **FilenameUtils.jav[0m[1;92ma:84[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m90[0m[39m** explicitly documents this exact vulnerability [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscenario:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   > [0m[32m"If a careless client used that filename as if it were a filename and not a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mpath when writing embedded files, bad things could happen. Consider: [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m`'../../../my_ppt.ppt'`"[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **FSUtil.jav[0m[1;92ma:199[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m200[0m[39m** shows an additional check pattern for rejecting absolute[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths upfront.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Primary Approach: Path Validation with Defense-in-Depth**[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must be applied to [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaUntar.java` in the `main` method, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically modifying the vulnerable code block at lines [0m[1;36m41[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m48[0m[39m.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Initial Path Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAfter Line [0m[1;36m43[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter resolving and normalizing the target path, add an immediate validation check:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that normalized path is within extraction directory[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal attempt detected in tar entry: "[0m[39m + [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for both paths to ensure consistent [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomparison[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` checks if target is a descendant of extractDir[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This catches most path traversal attempts early, before any filesystem operations[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Does not require the path to exist yet [0m[1;39m([0m[39munlike `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Add Secondary Real Path Validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAfter Line [0m[1;36m46[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter creating parent directories, add a stronger validation using `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Additional validation after directory creation to prevent symlink attacks[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtry [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal or symlink attack detected in tar [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mentry: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If [0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fails [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., path doesn't exist yet[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, that's acceptable[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m since we've already validated with [0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m above[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves symbolic links and provides stronger security[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This prevents symlink-based attacks where a symlink could be used to escape the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrapped in try-catch because `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` requires the path to exist[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Follows the exact pattern used in `FileSystemFetcher.jav[0m[1;92ma:79[0m[39m`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Complete Modified Code Block[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerable code at lines [0m[1;36m41[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m48[0m[39m should be transformed to:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtae != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.isFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Security check [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Validate normalized path is within extraction [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal attempt detected in tar entry: "[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Security check [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Additional validation after directory creation [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msymlink protection[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal or symlink attack detected in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mtar entry: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If [0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fails due to non-existent path, rely on first check[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Re-throw if it's a security violation detected by our check[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m != null && [0m[1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mtraversal"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                throw e;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mFiles.write[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtarget, [0m[1;35mtais.readAllBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    tae = [0m[1;35mtais.getNextEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why This is the Optimal Approach:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Functionality:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintains the original behavior of extracting files with their directory [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test cases like `TikaUntarTest.jav[0m[1;92ma:37[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m69[0m[39m` will continue to pass[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to the API or expected output format[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Defense-in-Depth Security:**[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two-layer validation provides redundancy[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - First check catches obvious traversal attempts efficiently[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Second check [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m provides maximum security against [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msophisticated attacks[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Follows established Tika security patterns from `FileSystemFetcher`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Minimal Code Changes:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only modifies the vulnerable method[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No import changes required [0m[1;39m([0m[39mall classes already available in `java.nio.file`[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to external interfaces or utility classes[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Addresses All Attack Vectors:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Blocks relative path traversal [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/../../etc/[0m[95mpasswd[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Blocks absolute paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/etc/[0m[95mpasswd[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Blocks symlink-based attacks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Handles edge cases where paths don't exist yet[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Consistent with Tika Philosophy:**[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The codebase already has awareness of this issue [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdocumented in [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilenameUtils.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses the same validation pattern as `FileSystemFetcher.java`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Provides informative error messages for security violations[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Addressing Potential Side Effects[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Concern [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Performance Impact**[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Mitigation: Validation checks are lightweight path operations[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` are fast string/path operations[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is slightly more expensive but only called after directory [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreation[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Impact is negligible compared to file I/O operations[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Concern [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Legitimate Tar Archives with Complex Paths**[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Mitigation: Any legitimate tar entry with a valid relative path will pass [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only malicious entries attempting to escape the extraction directory are blocked[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Archives created with standard tar utilities will work correctly[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Concern [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Breaking Existing Tests**[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Mitigation: The test `TikaUntarTest.java` uses legitimate tar files[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing tests should continue to pass[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only malicious test cases [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich don't currently exist[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m would be blocked[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Concern [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Cross-Platform Compatibility**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Mitigation: Uses `java.nio.file.Path` API which handles platform differences[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` work consistently across Windows/Unix/Mac[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Path separator handling is automatic[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Alternative Approaches Considered and Rejected[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Alternative [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Use [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to Strip Paths**[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mString safeName = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39msafeName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Rejected because:** This flattens the directory structure, losing the original [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtar layout[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Would break test expectations in `TikaUntarTest.jav[0m[1;92ma:64[0m[39m` which expects [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test-documents/` subdirectory[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changes the fundamental behavior of the utility[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Alternative [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Reject Only Absolute Paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFSUtil Pattern[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.isAbsolute[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Absolute paths not allowed"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Rejected because:** This only blocks one attack vector[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Doesn't prevent relative path traversal [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/../../[0m[95metc[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Insufficient security on its own[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Alternative [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Use Commons Compress Built-in Validation**[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Rejected because:** Apache Commons Compress doesn't provide path validation[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Would require external library modifications [0m[1;39m([0m[39mforbidden by fix strategy rules[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The security check must be in the application code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaUntar[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Locate the vulnerable code:** [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaUntar.jav[0m[1;92ma:41[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m48[0m[39m`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
